<TITLE> Ensure highest security during Puja: Tuku </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 24 (bdnews24.com)State minister for home affairs Shamsul Huq Tuku on Thursday ordered the law- enforcers to take maximum caution during the Durga Puja festivals. Tuku visited the Puja pavilions at Dhakeswari National Temple, Tantibazaar, Rayerbazar and Gabtoli, among others in Dhaka, and Ram Krishna Mission in Narayanganj. He enquired about security arrangements and gave some directives. Later, he told reporters the incumbent government will take every necessary step to ensure security and uproot terrorism. "We've given directives to the respective authorities to efficiently tackle any untoward situation." Police chief Noor Mohammad, RAB chief Hassan Mahmood Khandaker and Dhaka City police chief AKM Shahidul Huq accompanied with the junior minister. He visited Nur Jewelers at Gulshan Plaza, talked to the owners and ordered the police to grab the criminals immediately. Burglars broke into the shop and stole gold and other valuables said to be worth Tk 6 crore on the night of Eid. bdn
